TITLE: Handling Graceful Shutdown of Unleash SDK in AWS Lambda
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to handle graceful shutdown of the Unleash SDK in an AWS Lambda function. It listens for the SIGTERM signal and ensures that any outstanding metrics are flushed back to the Unleash API before the function instance is terminated.
SOURCE: https://github.com/unleash/unleash/blob/main/website/docs/feature-flag-tutorials/serverless/implementing-feature-flags-in-aws-lambda.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
let unleash;

process.on("SIGTERM", async () => {
    console.info("[runtime] SIGTERM received");

    if (unleash) {
        await destroyWithFlush();
        unleash = undefined;
    }

    process.exit(0);
});
```

